    <note>Zhao(1) Qinfu(2) [25577] According to Lu(5) You's funerary inscription for his father, Yanzhen [25578] (q.v.), he was the son-in-law of You's grandnephew and his wife's younger brother and he received the jinshi at the same sitting. Imperial clansmen were not included in the Shaoxing jinshi lists, but the only possible candidate for Qinfu(2)'s wife's younger brother was Lu(5) Ruochuan [13478], which would make his father, A [25576], a second grandnephew of You.</note>
